dex1: Roughly 20 years ago, it was artificially created, utilizing the latest technology of the time.
dex2: It can convert its body into digital data, which enables it to enter cyberspace.

dex1: Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.
dex2: An ancient POKéMON that was recovered from a fossil. It swims by cleverly twisting its 10 tentacles about.

dex1: A prehistoric POKéMON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.
dex2: Sharp beaks ring its mouth. Its shell was too big for it to move freely, so it became extinct.

dex1: A POKéMON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.
dex2: A POKéMON that was recovered from a fossil. It uses the eyes on its back while hiding on the sea floor.

dex1: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.
dex2: A slim and fast swimmer. It slices its prey with its sharp sickles and drinks the body fluids.

dex1: A Pokémon from the age of the dinosaurs. It used its sawlike fangs to shred its prey before eating them.
dex2: In ancient times, it ruled the skies. A widely accepted theory is that it went extinct due to a large meteor impact.

dex1: Its stomach is said to be incomparably strong. Even Muk’s poison is nothing more than a hint of spice on Snorlax’s tongue.
dex2: It eats nearly 900 pounds of food every day. It starts nodding off while eating—and continues to eat even while it’s asleep.

dex1: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.
dex2: A legendary bird POKéMON. It freezes water that is contained in winter air and makes it snow.

dex1: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.
dex2: This legendary bird POKéMON is said to appear when the sky turns dark and lightning showers down.

dex1: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.
dex2: A legendary bird POKéMON. As it flaps its flaming wings, even the night sky will turn red.

dex1: It grows by molting repeatedly. Boots made from the tanned cast-off skin are a super luxury item.
dex2: After a 10-hour struggle, a fisherman was able to pull one up and confirm its existence.

dex1: It has long been thought that its crystalline orbs are imbued with the power to control the weather.
dex2: From time immemorial, it has been venerated by agricultural peoples as an entity able to control the weather.

dex1: This Pokémon saved a shipwrecked man, taking him to a remote island—a paradise occupied solely by Dragonite.
dex2: Incur the wrath of this normally calm Pokémon at your peril, because it will smash everything to smithereens before it’s satisfied.

dex1: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.
dex2: Its DNA is almost the same as MEW’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

dex1: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.
dex2: When viewed through a microscope, this POKéMON’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.

dex1: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up the sun’s rays.
dex2: Its pleasantly aromatic leaves have the ability to check the humidity and temperature.

dex1: The scent of spices comes from around its neck. Somehow, sniffing it makes you want to fight.
dex2: A spicy aroma emanates from around its neck. The aroma acts as a stimulant to restore health.

dex1: The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.
dex2: MEGANIUM’s breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

dex1: It is timid, and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.
dex2: It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised, it shoots flames out of its back.

dex1: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.
dex2: This POKéMON is fully covered by nonflammable fur. It can withstand any kind of fire attack.

dex1: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.
dex2: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.

dex1: Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.
dex2: It is small but rough and tough. It won’t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.

dex1: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.
dex2: It opens its huge jaws wide when attacking. If it loses any fangs while biting, they grow back in.

dex1: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.
dex2: It is hard for it to support its own weight out of water, so it gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

dex1: A very cautious POKéMON, it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.
dex2: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.

dex1: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other POKéMON to enter.
dex2: There is no telling where the tail begins. Despite its short legs, it is quick at hunting RATTATA.

dex1: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.
dex2: It has a perfect sense of time. Whatever happens, it keeps rhythm by precisely tilting its head in time.

dex1: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.
dex2: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

dex1: They are timid and grow uneasy when not in a swarm with others of their kind. The pattern on their backs differs slightly from one to another.
dex2: They communicate with one another using bodily fluids that give off odors. When they’re angry, their odor smells sour.

dex1: While it’s believed that starlight provides it with energy, this Pokémon also loves to eat berries. In the daytime, it curls up in the grass to sleep.
dex2: In battle, it throws punches with all four arms. The power of each individual blow is piddly, so it aims to win by quantity rather than quality.

dex1: It waits intently until its preferred prey, Cutiefly, gets caught in its web. In fact, it’s quite a patient Pokémon.
dex2: Some fishermen weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

dex1: There are some areas where people use the string Ariados spins for their own weaving. The resulting cloth is popular for its strength.
dex2: It spins thread from both its rear and its mouth. Then it wraps its prey up in thread and sips their bodily fluids at its leisure.

dex1: Both its legs became wings, and as a result, it can’t move well on the ground. All it can do is crawl around.
dex2: Silent and swift in its four-winged flight, it bites down on its prey before they realize what’s happening. In a heartbeat, it drains their blood.

dex1: Its two antennae were originally fins. It discharges electricity to stun its prey before attacking.
dex2: It lives in the depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.

dex1: Should you peer into the ocean at night and see a light shining like the stars, that is Lanturn.
dex2: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.

dex1: It is not yet skilled at controlling electricity. If you take your eyes off it, it may shock itself.
dex2: Despite this Pokémon’s cute appearance, those who want to live with one should prepare to be on the receiving end of its electric jolts.

dex1: On late nights illuminated by shooting stars, it gazes intently skyward, as if thinking of its home.
dex2: Because of its silhouette, it’s believed to be a star reborn. For some reason, it loves Minior.

dex1: It likes to sing but is not yet good at it. With praise and encouragement, it will get better little by little.
dex2: It moves by bouncing along. As it moves a lot, it sweats, and its body gives off a sweet aroma.

dex1: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.
dex2: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping TOGEPI stand up.

dex1: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.
dex2: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.

dex1: Because its wings aren’t yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.
dex2: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.

dex1: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.
dex2: In South America, it is said that its right eye sees the future and its left eye views the past.

dex1: If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.
dex2: Its fleece grows continually. In the summer, the fleece is fully shed, but it grows back in a week.

dex1: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won’t grow.
dex2: Its fluffy fleece easily stores electricity. Its rubbery hide keeps it from being electrocuted.

dex1: The tail’s tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.
dex2: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.

dex1: BELLOSSOM gather at times and appear to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.
dex2: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

dex1: The tip of its tail, which contains oil that is lighter than water, lets it swim without drowning.
dex2: The end of its tail serves as a buoy that keeps it from drowning, even in a vicious current.

dex1: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.
dex2: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.

dex1: To avoid attack, it mimics a tree. It will run off if splashed with water, which it hates.
dex2: Apparently, the larger the green parts of this Pokémon, the more collectors value it. It’s a particular favorite among elderly people.

dex1: They gather on moonlit nights to form a large chorus. Their cries sound angry and not at all pleasant, but they are certainly distinctive.
dex2: It’s the leader of Poliwag and Poliwhirl. When Politoed roars, they all cower in fear.

dex1: To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. They do enjoy gentle breezes, though.
dex2: Its body is so light, it must grip the ground firmly with its feet to keep from being blown away.

dex1: The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluctuates up and down.
dex2: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.

dex1: Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores to float, even around the world.
dex2: Drifts on seasonal winds and spreads its cotton-like spores all over the world to make more offspring.

dex1: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.
dex2: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.

dex1: It may drop out of the sky suddenly. If attacked by a SPEAROW, it will violently shake its leaves.
dex2: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

dex1: It converts sunlight into energy. In the darkness after sunset, it closes its petals and becomes still.
dex2: In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic manner, but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.

dex1: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.
dex2: Its large eyes can scan 360 degrees. It looks in all directions to seek out insects as its prey.

dex1: This POKéMON lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.
dex2: When it walks around on the ground, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.

dex1: This carefree POKéMON has an easy-going nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.
dex2: Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on boulders and boat hulls as it swims.

dex1: It can instantaneously sense its opponent’s movements by feeling air currents with its fine fur.
dex2: It unleashes psychic power from the orb on its forehead. When its power is exhausted, the orb grows dull and dark.

dex1: When this Pokémon becomes angry, its pores secrete a poisonous sweat, which it sprays at its opponent’s eyes.
dex2: With its black fur, it blends into the darkness. It bides its time, and when prey appears, this Pokémon goes for its throat, and then eats it.

dex1: They awaken at dusk and take wing in the twilight, leading to the expression, “Get home before the Murkrow fly.”
dex2: Seen as a symbol of bad luck, it’s generally disliked. Yet it gives presents—objects that sparkle or shine—to Trainers it’s close to.

dex1: A poisonous bite reacted with its system, blessing it with the enhanced intellect of a genius. It has full control of its psychic powers.
dex2: This Pokémon is so famed for its intellect that a proverb still persists in some regions: “When in doubt, ask Slowking.”

dex1: It will use any means necessary to frighten people and absorb their life energy. It practices constantly to hone its skill in causing fear.
dex2: If you hear a sobbing sound emanating from a vacant room, it’s undoubtedly a bit of mischief from Misdreavus.

dex1: Their shapes look like hieroglyphs on ancient tablets. It is said that the two are somehow related.
dex2: Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.

dex1: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.
dex2: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

dex1: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent and bite.
dex2: Its tail, which also contains a small brain, may bite on its own if it notices an alluring smell.

dex1: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn’t bother it.
dex2: It hangs and waits for flying insect prey to come near. It does not move about much on its own.

dex1: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.
dex2: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

dex1: When spotted, this POKéMON escapes backward by furiously boring into the ground with its tail.
dex2: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can float just slightly using its wings.

dex1: It flies straight at its target’s face then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.
dex2: It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

dex1: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than a diamond.
dex2: It is said that if an ONIX lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

dex1: Despite its intimidating face, it’s quite cowardly. Its desperate attempts to appear threatening make it popular with people.
dex2: Its growls make its opponents uneasy. This laid-back Pokémon tends to sleep half the day.

dex1: Its well-developed lower jaw and heavy fangs are its weapons. As long as it’s not provoked, it rarely bites.
dex2: More timid than Snubbull, this Pokémon is doted on by young people amused at the contrast between its looks and its attitude.

dex1: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.
dex2: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.

dex1: It uses its wings to adjust its body temperature. Otherwise, its metal body would become too hot and melt in the heat of battle.
dex2: Once it has identified an enemy, this Pokémon smashes it mercilessly with pincers hard as steel.

dex1: The BERRIES it stores in its vase-like shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.
dex2: It stores BERRIES inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

dex1: This powerful POKéMON thrusts its prized horn under its enemies’ bellies then lifts and throws them.
dex2: Usually docile, but if disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

dex1: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.
dex2: It uses its claws to poke holes in eggs so it can slurp out the insides. Breeders consider it a scourge and will drive it away or eradicate it.

dex1: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they are soaked with honey.
dex2: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

dex1: Although it is a good climber, it prefers to snap trees with its forelegs and eat fallen BERRIES.
dex2: With its ability to distinguish any aroma, it unfailingly finds all food buried deep underground.

dex1: It never sleeps. It has to keep moving because if it stopped, its magma body would cool and harden.
dex2: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.

dex1: The shell on its back is just skin that has cooled and hardened. It breaks easily with a slight touch.
dex2: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.

dex1: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.
dex2: If it smells something enticing, it dashes headlong off to find the source of the aroma.

dex1: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.
dex2: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

dex1: Coral branches grow from its head. They break off quite easily, but they grow back in about three days.
dex2: Pursued by Mareanie for the branches on its head, this Pokémon will sometimes snap its own branches off as a diversion while it escapes.

dex1: It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike even moving prey from more than 300 feet.
dex2: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a MANTINE’s underside to scavenge for leftovers.

dex1: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles then smashes them with its rock-hard head.
dex2: It instinctively sneaks into rocky holes. If it gets sleepy, it steals the nest of a fellow OCTILLERY.

dex1: Although it naturally prefers colder locales, Delibird in Alola seem able to withstand the heat to a certain extent.
dex2: It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and Pokémon, so it’s always scrounging around for more food.

dex1: As it majestically swims, it doesn’t care if REMORAID attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.
dex2: Swimming freely in open seas, it may fly out of the water and over the waves if it builds up enough speed.

dex1: Its feathers, which fall off as it grows, are thin and sharp. In times long past, warriors used them as swords.
dex2: Its metal body is sturdy, but it does rust rather easily. So on rainy days, this Pokémon prefers to stay put in its nest.

dex1: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.
dex2: To corner prey, they check each other’s location using barks that only they can understand.

dex1: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.
dex2: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other POKéMON get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

dex1: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.
dex2: It sleeps deep on the ocean floor to build its energy. It is said to cause tornadoes as it wakes.

dex1: It swings its long snout around playfully, but because it is so strong, that can be dangerous.
dex2: As a sign of affection, it bumps with its snout. However, it is so strong, it may send you flying.

dex1: It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its TACKLE is strong enough to knock down a house.
dex2: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.

dex1: For the purposes of planetary development, Porygon was updated with the most cutting-edge technology available.
dex2: Porygon was updated to a new version in readiness for planetary development. But that dream remains unrealized as yet.

dex1: The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.
dex2: Those who stare at its antlers will gradually lose control of their senses and be unable to stand.

dex1: The unique creations produced by each Smeargle are painted using the fluid that oozes from its tail. This is how it marks its territory.
dex2: It draws symbols all over the place to mark its territory. In towns with many Smeargle, the walls are covered in graffiti.

dex1: It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.
dex2: Even though it is small, it can’t be ignored because it will slug any handy target without warning.

dex1: If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks, you may get drilled hard.
dex2: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

dex1: Its lips are the most sensitive parts on its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.
dex2: It always rocks its head slowly backwards and forwards as if it is trying to kiss someone.

dex1: When it’s in a house, electrical outlets serve as its baby bottles. It sucks down electricity.
dex2: This Pokémon is constantly fighting with Togedemaru that try to steal its electricity. It’s a pretty even match.

dex1: Many of these Pokémon can be seen in areas with volcanic activity. Feeding can get them so excited, they exhale flames of 1,100 degrees F.
dex2: A famous potter lives with a Magby. Apparently its soft flames produce fine works.

dex1: Its milk is high in calories and packed with nutrients. Therefore, if you drink too much of it, you may wind up with a body like Miltank’s.
dex2: Most people raise it for its milk, but it’s quite tough and strong, so it’s also well suited for battle.

dex1: Even the most ferocious Pokémon become calm when they eat Blissey’s egg, which is said to be filled with happiness.
dex2: Its fluffy fur coat acts as a sensor, enabling it to read the feelings of people and Pokémon.

dex1: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.
dex2: A POKéMON that races across the land while barking a cry that sounds like crashing thunder.

dex1: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Unable to restrain its extreme power, it races headlong around the land.
dex2: A POKéMON that races across the land. It is said that one is born every time a new volcano appears.

dex1: Said to be the reincarnation of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.
dex2: This POKéMON races across the land. It is said that north winds will somehow blow whenever it appears.

dex1: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.
dex2: It is born deep underground. It can’t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.

dex1: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its THRASHING can topple a mountain.
dex2: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

dex1: Its body can’t be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.
dex2: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.

dex1: It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.
dex2: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

dex1: Legends claim this POKéMON flies the world’s skies continuously on its magnificent seven-colored wings.
dex2: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

dex1: This POKéMON wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.
dex2: When CELEBI disappears deep in a forest, it is said to leave behind an egg it brought from the future.

dex1: TREECKO has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This POKéMON attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.
dex2: TREECKO is cool, calm, and collected - it never panics under any situation. If a bigger foe were to glare at this POKéMON, it would glare right back without conceding an inch of ground.

dex1: The leaves growing out of GROVYLE’s body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This POKéMON is a master at climbing trees in jungles.
dex2: This POKéMON adeptly flies from branch to branch in trees. In a forest, no POKéMON can ever hope to catch a fleeing GROVYLE however fast they may be.

dex1: The leaves growing on SCEPTILE’s body are very sharp edged. This POKéMON is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.
dex2: SCEPTILE has seeds growing on its back. They are said to be bursting with nutrients that revitalize trees. This POKéMON raises the trees in a forest with loving care.

dex1: TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER, following behind with unsteady steps. This POKéMON breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees F, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.
dex2: TORCHIC has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug - it will be glowing with warmth. This POKéMON is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

dex1: COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This POKéMON’s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out ten kicks in one second.
dex2: COMBUSKEN battles with the intensely hot flames it spews from its beak and with outstandingly destructive kicks. This POKéMON’s cry is very loud and distracting.

dex1: In battle, BLAZIKEN blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this POKéMON’s wrists burn.
dex2: BLAZIKEN has incredibly strong legs - it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This POKéMON’s blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

dex1: The fin on MUDKIP’s head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this POKéMON can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.
dex2: In water, MUDKIP breathes using the gills on its cheeks. If it is faced with a tight situation in battle, this POKéMON will unleash its amazing power - it can crush rocks bigger than itself.

dex1: The surface of MARSHTOMP’s body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This POKéMON plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.
dex2: MARSHTOMP is much faster at traveling through mud than it is at swimming. This POKéMON’s hindquarters exhibit obvious development, giving it the ability to walk on just its hind legs.

dex1: SWAMPERT is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This POKéMON also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.
dex2: SWAMPERT predicts storms by sensing subtle differences in the sounds of waves and tidal winds with its fins. If a storm is approaching, it piles up boulders to protect itself.

dex1: At first sight, POOCHYENA takes a bite at anything that moves. This POKéMON chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.
dex2: POOCHYENA is an omnivore - it will eat anything. A distinguishing feature is how large its fangs are compared to its body. This POKéMON tries to intimidate its foes by making the hair on its tail bristle out.

dex1: MIGHTYENA gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This POKéMON will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.
dex2: MIGHTYENA travel and act as a pack in the wild. The memory of its life in the wild compels the POKéMON to obey only those TRAINERS that it recognizes to possess superior skill.

dex1: ZIGZAGOON restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This POKéMON does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.
dex2: The hair on ZIGZAGOON’s back is  bristly. It rubs the hard back hair against trees to leave its territorial markings. This POKéMON may play dead to fool foes in battle.

dex1: LINOONE always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This POKéMON is very challenged by gently curving roads.
dex2: When hunting, LINOONE will make a beeline straight for the prey at a full run. While this POKéMON is capable of topping 60 mph, it has to come to a screeching halt before it can turn.

dex1: Using the spikes on its rear end,   WURMPLE peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This POKéMON’s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.
dex2: WURMPLE is targeted by SWELLOW as prey. This POKéMON will try to resist by pointing the spikes on its rear at the attacking predator. It will weaken the foe by leaking poison from the spikes.

dex1: SILCOON tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There,  this POKéMON hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.
dex2: SILCOON was thought to endure hunger and not consume anything before its evolution. However, it is now thought that this POKéMON slakes its thirst by drinking rainwater that collects on its silk.

dex1: BEAUTIFLY’s favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this POKéMON, just leave a potted flower by an open window. BEAUTIFLY is sure to come looking for pollen.
dex2: BEAUTIFLY has a long mouth like a coiled needle, which is very convenient for collecting pollen from flowers. This POKéMON rides the spring winds as it flits around gathering pollen.

dex1: CASCOON makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This POKéMON prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.
dex2: If it is attacked, CASCOON remains motionless however badly it may be hurt. It does so because if it were to move, its body would be weak upon evolution. This POKéMON will also not forget the pain it endured.

dex1: DUSTOX is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this POKéMON are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.
dex2: When DUSTOX flaps its wings, a fine dust is scattered all over. This dust is actually a powerful poison that will even make a pro wrestler sick. This POKéMON searches for food using its antennae like radar.

dex1: LOTAD live in ponds and lakes, where they float on the surface. It grows weak if its broad leaf dies. On rare occasions, this POKéMON travels on land in search of clean water.
dex2: LOTAD is said to have dwelled on land before. However, this POKéMON is thought to have returned to water because the leaf on its head grew large and heavy. It now lives by floating atop the water.

dex1: LOMBRE is nocturnal - it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief-maker. When this POKéMON spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.
dex2: LOMBRE’s entire body is covered by a slippery, slimy film. It feels horribly unpleasant to be touched by this POKéMON’s hands. LOMBRE is often mistaken for a human child.

dex1: LUDICOLO begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This POKéMON is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.
dex2: Upon hearing an upbeat and cheerful rhythm, the cells in LUDICOLO’s body become very energetic and active. Even in battle, this POKéMON will exhibit an amazing amount of power.

dex1: SEEDOT attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this POKéMON’s body becomes.
dex2: SEEDOT looks exactly like an acorn when it is dangling from a tree branch. It startles other POKéMON by suddenly moving. This POKéMON polishes its body once a day using leaves.

dex1: NUZLEAF live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This POKéMON dislikes having its long nose pinched.
dex2: This POKéMON pulls out the leaf on its head and makes a flute with it. The sound of NUZLEAF’s flute strikes fear and uncertainty in the hearts of people lost in a forest.

dex1: SHIFTRY is a mysterious POKéMON that is said to live atop towering trees  dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.
dex2: SHIFTRY’s large fans generate awesome gusts of wind at a speed close to 100 feet per second. The whipped-up wind blows anything away. This POKéMON chooses to live quietly deep in forests.

dex1: TAILLOW courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy POKéMON will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.
dex2: TAILLOW is young - it has only just left its nest. As a result, it sometimes becomes lonesome and cries at night. This POKéMON feeds on WURMPLE that live in forests.

dex1: SWELLOW flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This POKéMON dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by SWELLOW’s clawed feet, preventing escape.
dex2: SWELLOW is very conscientious about the upkeep of its glossy wings. Once two SWELLOW are gathered, they diligently take care of cleaning each other’s wings.

dex1: Its hollow bones enhance its lightness. It spreads its wings to the wind and soars away into the sky.
dex2: Fishermen keep an eye out for Wingull in the sky, because wherever they’re circling, the ocean is sure to be teeming with fish Pokémon.

dex1: Its spacious beak is large enough for a small child to fit right inside.
dex2: Gathering food is the work of young males. They store food in their capacious beaks and carry it back to others waiting in the nest.

dex1: RALTS senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This POKéMON rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.
dex2: RALTS has the ability to sense the emotions of people. If its TRAINER is in a cheerful mood, this POKéMON grows cheerful and joyous in the same way.

dex1: It is said that a KIRLIA that is exposed to the positive emotions of its TRAINER grows beautiful. This POKéMON controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.
dex2: KIRLIA uses the horns on its head to amplify its psychokinetic power. When the POKéMON uses its power, the air around it becomes distorted, creating mirages of nonexistent scenery.

dex1: GARDEVOIR has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its TRAINER, this POKéMON is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.
dex2: GARDEVOIR has the psychokinetic power to distort the dimensions and create a small black hole. This POKéMON will try to protect its TRAINER even at the risk of its own life.

dex1: It moves as if skating on the surface of the water. It often fights with Dewpider over food.
dex2: When this Pokémon senses danger, a sweet fluid oozes from the tip of its head. The taste of it disgusts bird Pokémon.

dex1: It intimidates enemies with the eye-like patterns on its antennae. Its four wings allow it to fly in any direction.
dex2: Its wings and antennae don’t cope well with moisture. After a rain, it faces sunward to dry off.

dex1: SHROOMISH live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This POKéMON feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.
dex2: If SHROOMISH senses danger, it shakes its body and scatters spores from the top of its head. This POKéMON’s spores are so toxic, they make trees and weeds wilt.

dex1: BRELOOM closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This POKéMON’s fighting technique puts boxers to shame.
dex2: The seeds ringing BRELOOM’s tail are made of hardened toxic spores. It is horrible to eat the seeds. Just taking a bite of this POKéMON’s seed will cause your stomach to rumble.

dex1: SLAKOTH lolls around for over twenty hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This POKéMON’s sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.
dex2: SLAKOTH’s heart beats just once a minute. Whatever happens, it is content to loaf around motionless. It is rare to see this POKéMON in motion.

dex1: VIGOROTH is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply can’t tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This POKéMON’s stress level rises if it can’t be moving constantly.
dex2: VIGOROTH is simply incapable of remaining still. Even when it tries to sleep, the blood in its veins grows agitated, compelling this POKéMON to run wild throughout the jungle before it can settle down.

dex1: SLAKING spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this POKéMON reluctantly moves to another spot.
dex2: Wherever SLAKING live, rings of over a yard in diameter appear in grassy fields. They are made by the POKéMON as it eats all the grass within reach while lying prone on the ground.

dex1: NINCADA lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This POKéMON absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.
dex2: NINCADA lives underground. It uses its sharp claws to carve the roots of trees and absorb moisture and nutrients. This POKéMON can’t withstand bright sunlight so avoids it.

dex1: NINJASK moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this POKéMON was long believed to be invisible.
dex2: If NINJASK is not trained properly, it will refuse to obey the TRAINER and cry loudly continuously. Because of this quality, this POKéMON is said to be one that puts the TRAINER’s abilities to the test.

dex1: SHEDINJA’s hard body doesn’t move - not even a twitch. In fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this POKéMON will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.
dex2: SHEDINJA is a peculiar POKéMON. It seems to appear unsought in a POKé BALL after a NINCADA evolves. This bizarre POKéMON is entirely immobile - it doesn’t even breathe.

dex1: Normally, WHISMUR’s voice is very quiet - it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this POKéMON senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.
dex2: WHISMUR is very timid. If it starts to cry loudly, it becomes startled by its own crying and cries even harder. When it finally stops crying, the POKéMON goes to sleep, all tired out.

dex1: LOUDRED’s bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. It uses its voice to punish its foes. This POKéMON’s round ears serve as loudspeakers.
dex2: LOUDRED shouts while stamping its feet. After it finishes shouting, this POKéMON becomes incapable of hearing anything for a while. This is considered to be a weak point.

dex1: EXPLOUD triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. If this POKéMON violently inhales from the ports on its body, it’s a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.
dex2: EXPLOUD communicates its feelings to the others by emitting whistle-like sounds from the tubes on its body. This POKéMON only raises its voice when it is in battle.

dex1: It was originally brought in from another region, but now Makuhita from Alola are more famous.
dex2: Their daily routine consists of training together first thing in the morning, eating and napping in the afternoon, and then more training afterward.

dex1: It is known for its fantastic strength, but as it grows older, it focuses more on training Makuhita.
dex2: They love to compare their freakish strength— strength enough to send a truck flying with a single slap.

dex1: AZURILL spins its tail as if it were a lasso, then hurls it far. The momentum of the throw sends its body flying, too. Using this unique action, one of these POKéMON managed to hurl itself a record 33 feet.
dex2: AZURILL’s tail is large and bouncy. It is packed full of the nutrients this POKéMON needs to grow. AZURILL can be seen bouncing and playing on its big, rubbery tail.

dex1: The magnet in Nosepass’s nose provides an unerring compass, making it an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.
dex2: It uses powerful magnetism to drag its prey toward it. It’s also been known to pull in metal, which it collects and uses to protect itself.

dex1: SKITTY has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This POKéMON is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.
dex2: SKITTY is known to chase around playfully after its own tail. In the wild, this POKéMON lives in holes in the trees of forests. It is very popular as a pet because of its adorable looks.

dex1: DELCATTY prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this POKéMON eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.
dex2: DELCATTY sleeps anywhere it wants without keeping a permanent nest. If other POKéMON approach it as it sleeps, this POKéMON will never fight - it will just move away somewhere else.

dex1: It’s a fiend for gemstones, so it stalks Carbink. Unfortunately, Gabite almost always grabs them first.
dex2: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it’s believed that Sableye will steal people’s spirits away.

dex1: MAWILE’s huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, MAWILE chomps it with its gaping jaws.
dex2: Don’t be taken in by this POKéMON’s cute face - it’s very dangerous. MAWILE fools the foe into letting down its guard, then chomps down with its massive jaws. The steel jaws are really horns that have been transformed.

dex1: This POKéMON has a body of steel. To make its body, ARON feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.
dex2: ARON has a body of steel. With one all-out charge, this POKéMON can demolish even a heavy dump truck. The destroyed dump truck then becomes a handy meal for the POKéMON.

dex1: LAIRON tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This POKéMON makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.
dex2: LAIRON feeds on iron contained in rocks and water. It makes its nest on mountains where iron ore is buried. As a result, the POKéMON often clashes with humans mining the iron ore.

dex1: AGGRON claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This POKéMON vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.
dex2: AGGRON is surprisingly protective of its environment. If its mountain is ravaged by a landslide or a fire, this POKéMON will haul topsoil to the area, plant trees, and beautifully restore its own territory.

dex1: MEDITITE undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this POKéMON always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.
dex2: MEDITITE heightens its inner energy through meditation. It survives on just one berry a day. Minimal eating is another aspect of this POKéMON’s training.

dex1: It is said that through meditation, MEDICHAM heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This POKéMON hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.
dex2: Through the power of meditation, MEDICHAM developed its sixth sense. It gained the ability to use psychokinetic powers. This POKéMON is known to meditate for a whole month without eating.

dex1: ELECTRIKE stores electricity in its long body hair. This POKéMON stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.
dex2: ELECTRIKE runs faster than the human eye can follow. The friction from running is converted into electricity, which is then stored in this POKéMON’s fur.

dex1: MANECTRIC is constantly discharging electricity from its mane. The sparks sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this POKéMON creates thunderclouds.
dex2: MANECTRIC discharges strong electricity from its mane. The mane is used for collecting electricity in the atmosphere. This POKéMON creates thunderclouds above its head.

dex1: PLUSLE always acts as a cheerleader for its partners. Whenever a teammate puts out a good effort in battle, this POKéMON shorts out its body to create the crackling noises of sparks to show its joy.
dex2: When PLUSLE is cheering on its partner, it flashes with electric sparks from all over its body. If its partner loses, this POKéMON cries loudly.

dex1: MINUN is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.
dex2: MINUN loves to cheer on its partner in battle. It gives off sparks from its body while it is doing so. If its partner is in trouble, this POKéMON gives off increasing amounts of sparks.

dex1: With the arrival of night, VOLBEAT emits light from its tail. It communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. This POKéMON is attracted by the sweet aroma of ILLUMISE.
dex2: VOLBEAT’s tail glows like a lightbulb. With other VOLBEAT, it uses its tail to draw geometric shapes in the night sky. This POKéMON loves the sweet aroma given off by ILLUMISE.

dex1: ILLUMISE attracts a swarm of VOLBEAT using a sweet fragrance. Once the VOLBEAT have gathered, this POKéMON leads the lit-up swarm in drawing geometric designs on the canvas of the night sky.
dex2: ILLUMISE leads a flight of illuminated VOLBEAT to draw signs in the night sky. This POKéMON is said to earn greater respect from its peers by composing more complex designs in the sky.

dex1: ROSELIA shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this POKéMON brings serenity to living things.
dex2: On extremely rare occasions, a ROSELIA is said to appear with its flowers in unusual colors. The thorns on this POKéMON’s head contain a vicious poison.

dex1: Virtually all of GULPIN’s body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This POKéMON’s stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.
dex2: Most of GULPIN’s body is made up of its stomach - its heart and brain are very small in comparison. This POKéMON’s stomach contains special enzymes that dissolve anything.

dex1: When SWALOT spots prey, it spurts out a hideously toxic fluid from its pores and sprays the target. Once the prey has weakened, this POKéMON gulps it down whole with its cavernous mouth.
dex2: SWALOT has no teeth, so what it eats, it swallows whole, no matter what. Its cavernous mouth yawns widely. An automobile tire could easily fit inside this POKéMON’s mouth.

dex1: Each school has its own territory. Any intruders are mercilessly attacked with fangs bared.
dex2: If they scent the faintest trace of blood, they rush to attack en masse. When alone, they’re rather cowardly.

dex1: It pursues its prey at speeds of 75 mph and finishes them off with fangs that can crush iron. It is known as the bully of the sea.
dex2: It has a sad history. In the past, its dorsal fin was a treasured foodstuff, so this Pokémon became a victim of overfishing.

dex1: It loves to startle people. It fills itself up with seawater and plays by bouncing around like a ball.
dex2: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

dex1: Wailord pursue their prey in pods. With their large mouths, they can swallow entire schools of Wishiwashi whole.
dex2: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

dex1: NUMEL is extremely dull witted - it doesn’t notice being hit. However, it can’t stand hunger for even a second. This POKéMON’s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.
dex2: NUMEL stores magma of almost 2,200 degrees F within its body. If it gets wet, the magma cools and hardens. In that event, the POKéMON’s body grows heavy and its movements become sluggish.

dex1: CAMERUPT has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees F courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this POKéMON’s back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.
dex2: The humps on CAMERUPT’s back are formed by a transformation of its bones. They sometimes blast out molten magma. This POKéMON apparently erupts often when it is enraged.

dex1: Coal is the source of Torkoal’s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.
dex2: If the fire burning within its shell goes out, it will die. Those who wish to raise one in their home must always keep something flammable at hand.

dex1: SPOINK bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. As a result, this POKéMON cannot afford to stop bouncing - if it stops, its heart will stop.
dex2: SPOINK keeps a pearl on top of its head. The pearl functions to amplify this POKéMON’s psychokinetic powers. It is therefore on a constant search for a bigger pearl.

dex1: GRUMPIG uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. When this POKéMON uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.
dex2: GRUMPIG uses the black pearls on its body to wield its fantastic powers. When it is doing so, it dances bizarrely. This POKéMON’s black pearls are valuable as works of art.

dex1: Its steps are staggering and unsteady, but Spinda thinks it’s walking in a straight line.
dex2: Each and every Spinda has a slightly different configuration of spots. There are collectors who enjoy the tiny differences in their spot patterns.

dex1: It can live for a week without eating a thing. It waits patiently at the bottom of its nest for prey to appear.
dex2: As it digs through the sand, its giant jaws crush any rocks that obstruct its path. It builds a funnel-shaped nest.

dex1: Rather than using its underdeveloped wings for flight, it rubs them together, producing ultrasonic waves to attack its enemies.
dex2: To help make its wings grow, it dissolves quantities of prey in its digestive juices and guzzles them down every day.

dex1: The flapping of its wings sounds something like singing. Those lured by the sound are enveloped in a sandstorm, becoming Flygon’s prey.
dex2: This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.

dex1: CACNEA lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this POKéMON shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.
dex2: The more arid and harsh the environment, the more pretty and fragrant a flower CACNEA grows. This POKéMON battles by wildly swinging its thorny arms.

dex1: During the daytime, CACTURNE remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This POKéMON becomes active at night when the temperature drops.
dex2: If a traveler is going through a desert in the thick of night, CACTURNE will follow in a ragtag group. The POKéMON are biding their time, waiting for the traveler to tire and become incapable of moving.

dex1: SWABLU has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. This POKéMON is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.
dex2: SWABLU loves to make things clean. If it spots something dirty, it will wipe and polish it with its cottony wings. If its wings become dirty, this POKéMON finds a stream and showers itself.

dex1: ALTARIA dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this POKéMON makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.
dex2: ALTARIA sings in a gorgeous soprano. Its wings are like cotton clouds. This POKéMON catches updrafts with its buoyant wings and soars way up into the wild blue yonder.

dex1: Memories of battling its arch-rival SEVIPER are etched into every cell of ZANGOOSE’s body. This POKéMON adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.
dex2: ZANGOOSE usually stays on all fours, but when angered, it gets up on its hind legs and extends its claws. This POKéMON shares a bitter rivalry with SEVIPER that dates back over generations.

dex1: SEVIPER shares a generations-long feud with ZANGOOSE. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This POKéMON attacks using its sword-edged tail.
dex2: SEVIPER’s swordlike tail serves two purposes - it slashes foes and douses them with secreted poison. This POKéMON will not give up its long-running blood feud with ZANGOOSE.

dex1: LUNATONE was discovered at a location where a meteorite fell. As a result, some people theorize that this POKéMON came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.
dex2: LUNATONE becomes active around the time of the full moon. Instead of walking, it moves by floating in midair. The POKéMON’s intimidating red eyes cause all those who see it to become transfixed with fear.

dex1: SOLROCK is a new species of POKéMON that is said to have fallen from space. It floats in air and moves silently. In battle, this POKéMON releases intensely bright light.
dex2: Sunlight is the source of SOLROCK’s power. It is said to possess the ability to read the emotions of others. This POKéMON gives off intense heat while rotating its body.

dex1: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey’s location.
dex2: Its slippery body is hard to grasp, so much so that there are festivals where people compete to see how many they can catch barehanded.

dex1: A glutton that devours anything that moves, it quietly lurks at the bottom of swamps, lying in wait for prey.
dex2: Sighting Whiscash leaping from the water is believed to herald an earthquake.

dex1: CORPHISH were originally foreign POKéMON that were imported as pets. They eventually turned up in the wild. This POKéMON is very hardy and has greatly increased its population.
dex2: CORPHISH catches prey with its sharp claws. It has no likes or dislikes when it comes to food - it will eat anything. This POKéMON has no trouble living in filthy water.

dex1: CRAWDAUNT has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this POKéMON, making them desolate places.
dex2: CRAWDAUNT molts (sheds) its shell regularly. Immediately after molting, its shell is soft and tender. Until the shell hardens, this POKéMON hides in its streambed burrow to avoid attack from its foes.

dex1: BALTOY moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this POKéMON living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.
dex2: As soon as it spots others of its kind, BALTOY congregates with them and then begins crying noisily in unison. This POKéMON sleeps while cleverly balancing itself on its one foot.

dex1: CLAYDOL are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This POKéMON moves about while levitating.
dex2: CLAYDOL is an enigma that appeared from a clay statue made by an ancient civilization dating back 20,000 years. This POKéMON shoots beams from both its hands.

dex1: LILEEP became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient POKéMON attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles  shaped like flower petals.
dex2: LILEEP is an ancient POKéMON that was regenerated from a fossil. It remains permanently anchored to a rock. From its immobile perch, this POKéMON intently scans for prey with its two eyes.

dex1: CRADILY roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This POKéMON freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.
dex2: CRADILY’s body serves as an anchor, preventing it from being washed away in rough seas. This POKéMON secretes a strong digestive fluid from its tentacles.

dex1: ANORITH was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive POKéMON once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.
dex2: ANORITH is said to be a type of  POKéMON predecessor, with eight wings at the sides of its body. This POKéMON swam in the primordial sea by undulating these eight wings.

dex1: ARMALDO’s tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This POKéMON’s two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.
dex2: ARMALDO is a POKéMON species that became extinct in prehistoric times. This POKéMON is said to have walked on its hind legs, which would have been more convenient for life on land.

dex1: A tough Pokémon that is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn’t popular.
dex2: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokémon’s marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.

dex1: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.
dex2: It lives at the bottom of clear lakes. In times of war, it shows itself, which soothes people’s minds and hearts.

dex1: It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.
dex2: Its form changes on its own, due to its cells’ sensitive reactions to temperature and humidity.

dex1: KECLEON is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception - this POKéMON can’t change the zigzag pattern on its belly.
dex2: KECLEON alters its body coloration to blend in with its surroundings, allowing it to sneak up on its prey unnoticed. Then it lashes out with its long, stretchy tongue to instantly ensnare the unsuspecting target.

dex1: SHUPPET is attracted by feelings of jealousy and vindictiveness. If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this POKéMON will appear in a swarm and line up beneath the eaves of that person’s home.
dex2: SHUPPET grows by feeding on dark emotions, such as vengefulness and  envy, in the hearts of people. It roams through cities in search of grudges that taint people.

dex1: BANETTE generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This POKéMON was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.
dex2: A cursed energy permeated the stuffing of a discarded and forgotten plush doll, giving it new life as BANETTE. The POKéMON’s energy would escape if it were to ever open its mouth.

dex1: DUSKULL can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this POKéMON chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.
dex2: DUSKULL wanders lost among the deep darkness of midnight. There is an oft-told admonishment given to misbehaving children that this POKéMON will spirit away bad children who earn scoldings from their mothers.

dex1: DUSCLOPS’s body is completely hollow - there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This POKéMON will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.
dex2: DUSCLOPS absorbs anything, however large the object may be. This POKéMON hypnotizes its foe by waving its hands in a macabre manner and by bringing its single eye to bear. The hypnotized foe is made to do DUSCLOPS’s bidding.

dex1: The bunches of fruit around TROPIUS’s neck are very popular with children. This POKéMON loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.
dex2: Children of the southern tropics eat as snacks the fruit that grows in bunches around the neck of TROPIUS. This POKéMON flies by flapping the leaves on its back as if they were wings.

dex1: CHIMECHO makes its cries echo inside its hollow body. When this POKéMON becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have the power to knock foes flying.
dex2: In high winds, CHIMECHO cries as it hangs from a tree branch or the eaves of a building using a suction cup on its head. This POKéMON plucks berries with its long tail and eats them.

dex1: Long ago, superstitions were spread about it, saying it brought disaster. This fed a hatred of it, and it was driven deep into the mountains.
dex2: Although it’s said to bring disaster, in actuality, this Pokémon possesses a calm disposition and warns people of any crises that loom.

dex1: WYNAUT can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this POKéMON will be slapping the ground with its tail.
dex2: WYNAUT gather on moonlit nights to play by squeezing up against each other. By being squeezed, this POKéMON gains endurance and is trained to dole out powerful counterattacks.

dex1: Their numbers seem to have rapidly increased in Alola. Custom has it that houses where Snorunt live will be prosperous for generations to come.
dex2: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit.

dex1: Legend says a boulder on an icy mountain absorbed the distress and regrets of a stranded mountaineer, giving rise to Glalie.
dex2: Its prey is instantaneously frozen stiff by the cold air it exhales from its huge mouth. While they’re in that frozen state, it gobbles them up.

dex1: SPHEAL is much faster rolling than  walking to get around. When groups of this POKéMON eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.
dex2: SPHEAL always travels by rolling around on its ball-like body. When the season for ice floes arrives, this POKéMON can be seen rolling about on ice and crossing the sea.

dex1: SEALEO has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This POKéMON occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a SPHEAL on its nose.
dex2: SEALEO often balances and rolls things on the tip of its nose. While the POKéMON is rolling something, it checks the object’s aroma and texture to determine whether it likes the object or not.

dex1: WALREIN’s two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing ten tons with one blow. This POKéMON’s thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.
dex2: WALREIN swims all over in frigid seawater while crushing icebergs with its grand, imposing tusks. Its thick layer of blubber makes enemy attacks bounce off harmlessly.

dex1: CLAMPERL’s sturdy shell is not only good for protection - it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown CLAMPERL’s shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.
dex2: CLAMPERL grows while being protected by its rock-hard shell. When its body becomes too large to fit inside the shell, it is sure evidence that this POKéMON is getting close to evolution.

dex1: HUNTAIL’s presence went unnoticed by people for a long time because it lives at extreme depths in the sea. This POKéMON’s eyes can see clearly even in the murky dark depths of the ocean.
dex2: HUNTAIL’s tail is shaped like a fish. It uses the tail to attract prey, then swallows the prey whole with its large, gaping mouth. This POKéMON swims by wiggling its slender body like a snake.

dex1: GOREBYSS lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this POKéMON’s body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.
dex2: Although GOREBYSS is the very picture of elegance and beauty while swimming, it is also cruel. When it spots prey, this POKéMON inserts its thin mouth into the prey’s body and drains the prey of its body fluids.

dex1: Its form has remained the same for one hundred million years. Its body is filled with fat, so it can withstand the water pressure of the deep sea.
dex2: It was fortuitously discovered during a deep sea expedition. Its teeth have atrophied, so it now survives on microscopic organisms it sucks up.

dex1: If a Luvdisc is left on its own, it becomes despondent, leaving itself open to attack. That is when Pelipper snatch them up.
dex2: Loving couples have a soft spot for this Pokémon, so honeymoon hotels often release this Pokémon into their pools.

dex1: Its belief that it will be able to fly one day is apparently the influence of information carried in its genes.
dex2: With its steel-hard stone head, it headbutts indiscriminately. This is because of the stress it feels at being unable to fly.

dex1: The cells within its shell transform with explosive speed, preparing it for evolution.
dex2: They lurk deep within caves—motionless, neither eating nor drinking. Why they don’t die is not known.

dex1: When angered, it loses all sense of itself and destroys everything around it. The destruction will continue until Salamence has tired itself out.
dex2: It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up the fields it passes over.

dex1: Its cells are all magnets. It uses magnetism to communicate with others of its kind.
dex2: With magnetic traction, it pulls its opponents in close. When they’re in range, it slashes them with its rear claws.

dex1: When two Beldum link together, their psychic power is doubled. Their intelligence, however, remains unchanged.
dex2: It adores magnetic minerals, so it pursues Nosepass at speeds exceeding 60 mph.

dex1: It firmly pins its prey using its four claws and large body. Then the teeth in the mouth on its stomach chew the prey to bits.
dex2: A linkage of two Metang, this Pokémon can perform any calculation in a flash by utilizing parallel processing in its four brains.

dex1: REGIROCK was sealed away by people long ago. If this POKéMON’s body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.
dex2: REGIROCK’s body is composed entirely of rocks. Recently, a study made the startling discovery that the rocks were all unearthed from different locations.

dex1: REGICE’s body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can’t be melted, even by fire. This POKéMON controls frigid air of minus 328 degrees F.
dex2: REGICE cloaks itself with frigid air of negative 328 degrees F. Things will freeze solid just by going near this POKéMON. Its icy body is so cold, it will not melt even if it is immersed in magma.

dex1: REGISTEEL has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this POKéMON eats.
dex2: REGISTEEL was imprisoned by people in ancient times. The metal composing its body is thought to be a curious substance that is not of this earth.

dex1: LATIAS is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this POKéMON ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.
dex2: LATIAS is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The POKéMON enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

dex1: LATIOS has the ability to make its foe see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This POKéMON is intelligent and understands human speech.
dex2: LATIOS will only open its heart to a TRAINER with a compassionate spirit. This POKéMON can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

dex1: KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKéMON saved people who were suffering from droughts.
dex2: KYOGRE is named in mythology as the POKéMON that expanded the sea by covering the land with torrential rains and towering tidal waves. It took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with GROUDON.

dex1: GROUDON has long been described in  mythology as the POKéMON that raised lands and expanded continents. This POKéMON took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.
dex2: GROUDON has the power to scatter rain clouds and make water evaporate with light and heat. It came as a savior to people who had been suffering from terrible floods.

dex1: RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth’s ozone layer,  never descending to the ground. This POKéMON appears to feed on water and particles in the atmosphere.
dex2: RAYQUAZA is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth’s ozone layer, above the clouds. Its existence had been completely unknown because it lived so high in the sky.

dex1: A legend states that JIRACHI will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this POKéMON senses danger, it will fight without awakening.
dex2: JIRACHI will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

dex1: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS. The crystalline organ on this POKéMON’s chest appears to be its brain.
dex2: DEOXYS emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This POKéMON shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

dex1: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.
dex2: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

dex1: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.
dex2: The shell is hardened soil. Some Pokémon come to peck the berries growing on the trees on its back.

dex1: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.
dex2: Groups of this Pokémon migrating in search of water have been mistaken for “moving forests.”

dex1: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.
dex2: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

dex1: To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.
dex2: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

dex1: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.
dex2: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

dex1: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.
dex2: It lives along shores in northern countries. A skilled swimmer, it dives for over 10 minutes to hunt.

dex1: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.
dex2: Its wings deliver wicked blows that snap even the thickest of trees. It searches for prey in icy seas.

dex1: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.
dex2: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

dex1: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.
dex2: Usually with a large flock, it is barely noticeable when alone. Its cries are very strident.

dex1: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.
dex2: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

dex1: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.
dex2: The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.

dex1: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.
dex2: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

dex1: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.
dex2: While its movements out of water are sluggish, it can swim as fast as any FEEBAS.

dex1: It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.
dex2: It chats with others using the sounds of its colliding antennae. These sounds are fall hallmarks.

dex1: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.
dex2: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

dex1: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.
dex2: Its forelegs have a muscle-based system of generating electricity. Its body shines if endangered.

dex1: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.
dex2: It rests its forelegs on others to communicate with rhythmic electric pulses from its claws.

dex1: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.
dex2: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hiding prey--even those taking shelter behind a wall.

dex1: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.
dex2: It lives alongside clear ponds. It scatters pollen that induces harsh sneezing and runny noses.

dex1: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.
dex2: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

dex1: It lived in jungles around a hundred million years ago. It used its skillful headbutts to combat Aerodactyl.
dex2: In rock layers where Cranidos fossils are found, the fossilized trunks of trees snapped in two are also often found.

dex1: The result of repeated headbutts is a skull grown thick and hard. However, its brain has shrunk in size compared with Cranidos’s.
dex2: Records exist of a revived fossil that evolved into Rampardos. It proceeded to escape and then destroy a skyscraper with a headbutt.

dex1: Many fossils of this Pokémon have been found, but almost none have shown signs of damage to the face.
dex2: This Pokémon lived in primeval jungles. Few enemies would have been willing to square off against its heavily armored face, so it’s thought.

dex1: While it can guard against any sort of attack from the front, it is left without recourse when attacked from behind.
dex2: It lived in the same environments as Rampardos. Their fossils have been found together— seemingly from after they’d fought to the finish.

dex1: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.
dex2: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

dex1: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.
dex2: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

dex1: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.
dex2: It does not keep a nest. It flies over fields and mountains in constant search of floral honey.

dex1: A Pokémon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.
dex2: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

dex1: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by COMBEE.
dex2: When endangered, grubs from its six-cell honeycomb strike back. There is only one in a colony.

dex1: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.
dex2: It makes electricity with pouches in its cheeks and shoots charges from its tail. It lives atop trees.

dex1: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.
dex2: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

dex1: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.
dex2: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

dex1: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.
dex2: Sunlight colors it red. When the small ball is drained of nutrients, it shrivels to herald evolution.

dex1: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.
dex2: It is docile as a bud, but turns cheerful when it blooms. It folds back into a bud if sunlight wanes.

dex1: For the most part, it makes its home along the seashore. Its color and form differ according to its habitat and the quality of its food.
dex2: Purple mucus sticks to the hands of anyone who touches it. Take care, as the substance is troublesome to wash off.

dex1: It has strong regenerative capabilities. Even if parts of it are bitten off by fish Pokémon, it will return to normal within a few hours.
dex2: Plankton, invisible to the naked eye, is its main food source. It comes onto the land periodically, but the reason for this is not known.

dex1: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.
dex2: They work in large colonies and make rings by linking their tails, apparently in friendship.

dex1: Stories go that it grabs the hands of small children and drags them away to the afterlife. It dislikes heavy children.
dex2: If for some reason its body bursts, its soul spills out with a screaming sound.

dex1: There was once an incident in which a man took a trip riding a Drifblim, only to go missing.
dex2: Even while under careful observation, large flocks of Drifblim flying at dusk will inexplicably disappear from view.

dex1: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.
