dex2: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

dex1: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.
dex2: It is very conscious of its looks and never fails to groom its ears. It runs with sprightly jumps.

dex1: It appears as if from nowhere—muttering incantations, placing curses, and giving people terrifying visions.
dex2: Mismagius have been known to cast spells to make people fall in love, so some people search for this Pokémon as if their life depended on it.

dex1: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than a hundred of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.
dex2: If its Murkrow cronies fail to catch food for it, or if it feels they have betrayed it, it will hunt them down wherever they are and punish them.

dex1: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.
dex2: With its sharp glare, it puts foes in a mild hypnotic state. It is a very fickle Pokémon.

dex1: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon’s nest and claims it as its own.
dex2: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

dex1: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.
dex2: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound. It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.

dex1: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.
dex2: It sprays a nose-curling, stinky fluid from its rear to repel attackers.

dex1: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.
dex2: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

dex1: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.
dex2: X-ray photos were taken to check its body structure. Nothing appeared, however.

dex1: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.
dex2: It can summon rain clouds. People long ago revered it as the bringer of plentiful harvests.

dex1: It does not deal well with water, so it lives in dry locales. Since its surroundings tend to lack greenery, it stands out noticeably.
dex2: From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from its body. This liquid is similar in composition to human sweat.

dex1: It does its absolute best to mimic the movements and expressions of its opponents, but it’s still not very good at it.
dex2: When this gifted mimic surprises an opponent, Mime Jr. feels so happy that it ends up forgetting it was imitating something.

dex1: It carries a round white rock in its belly pouch. If it gets along well with someone, it will sometimes give that person the rock.
dex2: It’s too small to lay eggs yet. As a surrogate, it searches out round white stones.

dex1: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.
dex2: It keeps rhythm by flicking its tail feathers like a metronome. It imitates human speech.

dex1: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.
dex2: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

dex1: It lives in caves warmed by geothermal heat. Even so, when the weather gets cold, it will huddle close with others of its kind.
dex2: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

dex1: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.
dex2: Shiny objects are its passion. It can be found in its cave, scarcely moving, its gaze fixed on the jewels it’s amassed or Carbink it has caught.

dex1: It can fly at speeds rivaling jet planes. It dives into flocks of bird Pokémon and gulps the entire flock down whole.
dex2: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.

dex1: It needs to consume its own weight in food every day. As far as flavor is concerned, it’s indifferent.
dex2: When it finds something that looks like it might be edible, it goes right ahead and swallows it whole. That’s why it gets fatter day by day.

dex1: It can discern the physical and emotional states of people, Pokémon, and other natural things from the shape of their aura waves.
dex2: It’s tough enough to run right through the night, and it’s also a hard worker, but it’s still just a youngster.

dex1: Not only does it perceive auras, but it has also gained the power to control them. It employs them in battle.
dex2: They can detect the species of a living being— and its emotions—from over half a mile away. They control auras and hunt their prey in packs.

dex1: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.
dex2: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

dex1: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.
dex2: Its huge mouth is almost seven feet across. It has enough power to completely crush a car.

dex1: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.
dex2: It lives in arid lands. It buries itself in sand and lies in wait for unsuspecting prey.

dex1: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.
dex2: Its body is encased in a sturdy shell. Its head rotates 180 degrees, eliminating blind spots.

dex1: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.
dex2: Inflating its poison sacs, it makes an eerie blubbering sound for intimidation.

dex1: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.
dex2: The toxin made in its poison sacs is pumped to the knuckle claws through tubes down its arms.

dex1: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.
dex2: Hanging from branches using its tentacles, it looks like a plant. It awaits prey, mouth wide open.

dex1: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.
dex2: Its double tail fins propel its energetic jumps. When it breaks the surface of the sea, Wingull swoop down to grab it on the fly.

dex1: With its shining light, it lures its prey close. However, the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokémon—its natural predators.
dex2: This deep-sea Pokémon lives at the bottom of the sea. Its fins haul it over the seabed in search of its favorite food—Starmie.

dex1: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.
dex2: Scientists discovered that the distinctive patterns on its back differ by region.

dex1: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.
dex2: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

dex1: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.
dex2: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as “The Ice Monster.”

dex1: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.
dex2: They dwell in cold places. This Pokémon’s main food source in Alola is Vulpix and Sandshrew, which they carefully divide among their group.

dex1: Three units generate magnetism. There have been many mistaken reports of UFO sightings when Magnezone flies through the night sky.
dex2: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin, while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

dex1: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.
dex2: The long tongue is always soggy with slobber. The saliva contains a solvent that causes numbness.

dex1: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. GEODUDE are shot at rare times.
dex2: It can launch a rock held in its hand like a missile by tightening then expanding muscles instantly.

dex1: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.
dex2: Its arms are made of plants that bind themselves to things. They grow back right away if cut.

dex1: It pushes the tips of its tails against its foes and then lets loose a high-voltage current. Its foes are burned to a crisp in an instant.
dex2: When it gets excited, it thumps its chest. With every thud, thunder roars and electric sparks shower all around.

dex1: They dwell in volcanic craters. According to what is known, a single pair of male and female Magmortar lives in one volcano.
dex2: From its arm, it launches fireballs hotter than 3,500 degrees Fahrenheit. Its arm starts to melt when it fires a whole barrage.

dex1: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.
dex2: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another’s rights and avoid needless strife.

dex1: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.
dex2: Its jaw power is incredible. It is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed.

dex1: Its cellular composition is closer to that of a plant than an animal. It uses photosynthesis to produce its energy supply without eating food.
dex2: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.

dex1: It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.
dex2: It freezes its fur into icicles, spiky and sharp, and tackles its prey.

dex1: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!
dex2: If it succeeds in catching even a faint breeze properly, it can circle the globe without flapping once.

dex1: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.
dex2: A frozen one was dug up from soil dating back 10,000 years. It woke up to much amazement.

dex1: In order to create a more advanced Pokémon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.
dex2: Its program was modified to facilitate extra-dimensional activities, but that led to noticeably strange behavior.

dex1: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.
dex2: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

dex1: It radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances become unusable.
dex2: The main body controls three mobile units called Mini-Noses, which it maneuvers to catch prey.

dex1: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.
dex2: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.

dex1: When it finds humans or Pokémon it likes, it freezes them and takes them to its chilly den, where they become decorations.
dex2: The soul of a woman lost on a snowy mountain possessed an icicle, becoming this Pokémon. The food it most relishes is the souls of men.

dex1: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
dex2: Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

dex1: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.
dex2: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.

dex1: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.
dex2: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake’s surface.

dex1: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.
dex2: It is thought that UXIE, MESPRIT and AZELF all came from the same egg.

dex1: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.
dex2: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when DIALGA was born.

dex1: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.
dex2: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

dex1: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.
dex2: Its body is made of rugged steel. However, it is partially melted in spots because of its own heat.

dex1: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.
dex2: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

dex1: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.
dex2: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

dex1: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
dex2: On nights around the quarter moon, the aurora from its tail extends and undulates beautifully.

dex1: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.
dex2: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

dex1: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.
dex2: Water makes up 80% of its body. This Pokémon is easily affected by its environment.

dex1: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.
dex2: Folklore has it that on moonless nights, this Pokémon will make people see horrific nightmares.

dex1: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.
dex2: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

dex1: It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.
dex2: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

dex1: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
dex2: It creates an unlimited supply of energy inside its body, which it shares with those who touch it.

dex1: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.
dex2: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

dex1: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.
dex2: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.

dex1: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.
dex2: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.

dex1: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.
dex2: It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.

dex1: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.
dex2: Whatever it eats becomes fuel for the flame in its stomach. When it is angered, the intensity of the flame increases.

dex1: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.
dex2: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

dex1: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.
dex2: The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.

dex1: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.
dex2: Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.

dex1: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
dex2: Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.

dex1: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.
dex2: Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.

dex1: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.
dex2: They make the patterns on their bodies shine in order to threaten predators. Keen eyesight lets them see in the dark.

dex1: Because it doesn’t yelp, it’s extremely popular with Trainers who live in apartment buildings.
dex2: The long fur surrounding its face functions as radar, enabling it to probe the condition of its battle opponents.

dex1: Its dense black fur grows continuously. The high cost of keeping its hard fur properly groomed makes this a troublesome Pokémon to train.
dex2: This Pokémon obeys its master’s orders faithfully. However, it refuses to listen to anything said by a person it doesn’t respect.

dex1: Intelligent, good-natured, and valiant, it’s a trustworthy partner on rescue teams.
dex2: With this wise Pokémon, there could be no concern that it would ever attack people. Some parents even trust it to babysit.

dex1: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.
dex2: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.

dex1: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.
dex2: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

dex1: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.
dex2: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.

dex1: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
dex2: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokémon is wild tempered.

dex1: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.
dex2: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600° F.

dex1: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.
dex2: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

dex1: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.
dex2: It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.

dex1: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.
dex2: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.

dex1: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.
dex2: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.

dex1: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.
dex2: With the mist from its forehead, it can create shapes of things from dreams it has eaten.

dex1: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.
dex2: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

dex1: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.
dex2: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.

dex1: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.
dex2: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

dex1: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.
dex2: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

dex1: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
dex2: This ill-tempered Pokémon is dangerous because when it’s angry, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

dex1: Born deep within the ground, it compares itself with similar species, such as Geodude and Carbink, to settle which has the hardest body.
dex2: The hexagonal cavity is its ear. It walks in the direction of sounds it hears, but if the sounds cease, it panics and topples over.

dex1: Its orange crystal is a mass of energy. Just one crystal fragment would provide enough fuel for a hundred dump trucks.
dex2: It explores caves in search of underground water. It’s not comfortable around water, so this Pokémon takes great care in lapping it up.

dex1: The blasts of energy it makes from sunbeams have terrifying power. However, it’s not able to fire its blasts at night or on rainy days.
dex2: Known for its hefty horsepower, this Pokémon is a popular partner for construction workers.

dex1: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.
dex2: Suction from its nostrils enables it to stick to cave walls during sleep. It leaves a heart-shaped mark behind.

dex1: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.
dex2: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

dex1: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.
dex2: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.

dex1: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.
dex2: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

dex1: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.
dex2: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radarlike ability to understand its surroundings through slight sounds.

dex1: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.
dex2: These Pokémon appear at building sites and help out with construction. They always carry squared logs.

dex1: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.
dex2: They strengthen their bodies by carrying steel beams. They show off their big muscles to their friends.

dex1: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.
dex2: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.

dex1: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.
dex2: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

dex1: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.
dex2: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.

dex1: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.
dex2: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.

dex1: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.
dex2: When they encounter foes bigger than themselves, they try to throw them. They always travel in packs of five.

dex1: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.
dex2: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

dex1: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.
dex2: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

dex1: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.
dex2: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

dex1: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.
dex2: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

dex1: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.
dex2: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.

dex1: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.
dex2: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

dex1: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.
dex2: Highly aggressive, it uses the claws near its neck to dig into its opponents and poison them.

dex1: When it finds others of its kind, they all stick together. When enough of them have collected, the mass resembles a cumulonimbus cloud.
dex2: Pillows and beds stuffed with cotton exhaled by Cottonee are soft and puffy, light and airy— altogether top quality.

dex1: It rides on the wind and slips into people’s homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton- filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.
dex2: This Pokémon appears, riding upon the wind. But if the wind gusts up, it’ll blow the cotton on this Pokémon’s head clean off.

dex1: Although the leaves on its head are bitter enough to cause dizziness, they provide relief from weariness—even more so when boiled.
dex2: By pruning the leaves on its head with regularity, this Pokémon can be grown into a fine plump shape.

dex1: No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.
dex2: As soon as it finds a male to be its partner, the beautiful flower on its head darkens, droops, and withers away.

dex1: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.
dex2: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other’s school.

dex1: It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.
dex2: It conceals itself in the sand and chomps down on the legs of any prey that unwarily walk over it. Its favorite food is Trapinch.

dex1: They move in groups of a few individuals. A female is often the leader of the group, and the males will gather food.
dex2: Thanks to the special membrane covering its eyes, it can see its surroundings clearly, even in the middle of the night.

dex1: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.
dex2: After clamping down with its powerful jaws, it twists its body around to rip its prey in half.

dex1: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.
dex2: Darumaka’s droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.

dex1: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
dex2: When weakened in battle, it transforms into a stone statue. Then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.

dex1: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.
dex2: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

dex1: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.
dex2: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

dex1: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.
dex2: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.

dex1: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.
dex2: It immediately headbutts anyone that makes eye contact with it. Its skull is massively thick.

dex1: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.
dex2: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.

dex1: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.
dex2: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

dex1: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.
dex2: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.

dex1: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.
dex2: They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are covered in pure gold.

dex1: Based on studies of its skeletal structure, it can apparently dive to ocean depths of over half a mile.
dex2: Reputed to be the ancestor of most turtle Pokémon, it lived in warm seas approximately a hundred million years ago.

dex1: It constructed its sturdy shell by crunching and swallowing the hard shells or bones of its prey.
dex2: Active both on land and in the sea, this Pokémon drags its land-based prey into the water to finish it off.

dex1: It is the ancestor of all bird Pokémon. Archen itself could not actually fly but moved by hopping from treetop to treetop.
dex2: To all appearances flightless, it was able to glide down from tall treetops to snag its prey.

dex1: Although apparently able to fly, they tended to run along the ground, averaging speeds of roughly 25 mph.
dex2: They hunted in flocks. When one Archeops had the prey cornered, another would swoop on it.

dex1: Unsanitary places are what they like best. They can be spotted in Alola, often with Grimer in hot pursuit.
dex2: It gorges on trash until its stomach is full. Then it belches toxic gas. An unlucky whiff of gas will put a person in the hospital.

dex1: Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots from its right arm. If even a little of it gets on you, you’ll experience the effects of the unidentified toxin.
dex2: For a time, their numbers increased explosively in Alola. Since the arrival of Grimer, their population has decreased dramatically.

dex1: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.
dex2: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

dex1: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.
dex2: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

dex1: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.
dex2: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

dex1: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.
dex2: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.

dex1: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.
dex2: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

dex1: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.
dex2: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.

dex1: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.
dex2: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers’ life spans.

dex1: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.
dex2: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they can survive in any environment.

dex1: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.
dex2: When their brains, now divided in two, are thinking the same thoughts, these Pokémon exhibit their maximum power.

dex1: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.
dex2: These remarkably intelligent Pokémon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.

dex1: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.
dex2: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.

dex1: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.
dex2: It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.

dex1: Born of an icicle, this Pokémon uses its frosty breath to make ice crystals, causing snow to fall.
dex2: It feels pleasantly cool when embraced. This Pokémon is treasured by households in warm regions.

dex1: Hot days cause its body to melt. It can be restored by refreezing it, but the process leaves its body slightly warped.
dex2: This Pokémon has existed since the Ice Age. It controls particles of ice, freezes its opponents, and then shatters them with a headbutt.

dex1: Each of its two heads has a brain, and when they are in agreement, it attacks its enemies by exhaling a violent blizzard.
dex2: Even if it loses one of its heads, it can live relatively problem-free. It makes snow clouds inside its body.

dex1: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.
dex2: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon’s fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

dex1: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.
dex2: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

dex1: It glides using its cape-like membrane. Electrical energy scatters from it, shocking its friends and foes alike.
dex2: It grills berries and bug Pokémon with electric shocks and makes a meal of them. It usually nests in the holes gouged in trees by Pikipek.

dex1: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.
dex2: When they feel threatened, they spit an acidic liquid to drive attackers away. This Pokémon targets Shelmet.

dex1: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.
dex2: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

dex1: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.
dex2: For some reason, this Pokémon resembles a Poké Ball. They release poison spores to repel those who try to catch them.

dex1: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.
dex2: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

dex1: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.
dex2: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag them down to their lairs, five miles below the surface.

dex1: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.
dex2: They propel themselves by expelling absorbed seawater from their bodies. Their favorite food is life energy.

dex1: It uses its special mucus to close the wounds of injured Pokémon. The reason for this behavior remains unknown.
dex2: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokémon gather in the area around Alomomola.

dex1: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.
dex2: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

dex1: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.
dex2: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.

dex1: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.
dex2: They stick their spikes into cave walls and absorb the minerals they find in the rock.

dex1: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.
dex2: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

dex1: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.
dex2: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.

dex1: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.
dex2: Spinning minigears are rotated at high speed and repeatedly fired away. It is dangerous if the gears don’t return.

dex1: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.
dex2: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

dex1: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.
dex2: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.

dex1: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.
dex2: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

dex1: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.
dex2: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.

dex1: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.
dex2: This Pokémon had never been seen until it appeared from far in the desert 50 years ago.

dex1: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.
dex2: It uses psychic power to control an opponent’s brain and tamper with its memories.

dex1: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.
dex2: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.

dex1: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.
dex2: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

dex1: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.
dex2: Being consumed in Chandelure’s flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.

dex1: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.
dex2: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

dex1: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.
dex2: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.

dex1: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.
dex2: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

dex1: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.
dex2: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.

dex1: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.
dex2: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

dex1: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.
dex2: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.

dex1: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.
dex2: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

dex1: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.
dex2: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.

dex1: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.
dex2: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

dex1: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.
dex2: They have mastered elegant combos. As they concentrate, their battle moves become swifter and more precise.

dex1: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.
dex2: They use the long fur on their arms as a whip to strike their opponents.

dex1: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.
dex2: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.

dex1: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.
dex2: These Pokémon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.

dex1: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.
dex2: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.

dex1: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.
dex2: They fight at Bisharp’s command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.

dex1: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.
dex2: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

dex1: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.
dex2: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.

dex1: They pick fights indiscriminately. They grow stronger and more powerful each time they faint or are injured.
dex2: With its sharp claws, this Pokémon pierces its prey, and then it pecks at them. Although it also consumes berries, it’s a carnivore at heart.

dex1: With its brave disposition, it fears nothing—not even death. Ancient Alolan people respected it, referring to it as “the hero of the sky.”
dex2: It’s thought that people disturbed their habitats in the past, so Braviary banded together to fight back.

dex1: It protects its plump posterior with the bones of prey it has consumed. As it grows, it replaces the bones.

dex1: They adorn themselves beautifully with bones. This is supposedly an effort to attract males, but no male Mandibuzz have ever been found.
dex2: It circles in the sky, keeping a keen eye out for Pokémon in a weakened state. Its choicest food is Cubone.

dex1: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.

dex1: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

dex1: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.
dex2: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

dex1: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.
dex2: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.

dex1: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.
dex2: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.

dex1: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

dex1: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.
dex2: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.

dex1: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

dex1: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.
dex2: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

dex1: This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

dex1: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

dex1: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

dex1: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

dex1: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

dex1: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

dex1: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

dex1: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

dex1: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.
dex2: Many famous songs have been inspired by the melodies that Meloetta plays.

dex1: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.
dex2: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.

dex1: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

dex1: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

dex1: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

dex1: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

dex1: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

dex1: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

dex1: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

dex1: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

dex1: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

dex1: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.

dex1: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

dex1: This amiable Pokémon is easy to train. But when battle is joined, it shows its ferocious side.
dex2: When it’s excited, its temperature can double, spiking hormone production in its body.

dex1: From its beak, it fires embers at its prey. Once it has caught them, it grills them at high heat before feasting upon them.

dex1: Its favorite foods are Wingull and Pikipek. It attacks with a powerful kick and grasps them firmly in its talons.

dex1: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

dex1: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

dex1: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

dex1: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

dex1: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.

dex1: This Pokémon can draw forth the power hidden within blooming wild flowers. It is particularly fond of red flowers.

dex1: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

dex1: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

dex1: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

dex1: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

dex1: It grows up imitating the behavior of Pangoro, which it looks up to as a leader.

dex1: It boasts superb physical strength. Those who wish to become Pangoro’s Trainer have no choice but to converse with their fists.
dex2: From the slight twitches of its bamboo leaf, it deduces its opponent’s movements. It’s eager to tussle but kindhearted toward its companions.

dex1: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

dex1: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

dex1: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

dex1: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

dex1: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.

dex1: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.

dex1: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.

dex1: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.

dex1: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

dex1: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.

dex1: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

dex1: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.

dex1: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

dex1: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

dex1: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

dex1: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

dex1: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

dex1: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

dex1: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

dex1: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

dex1: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

dex1: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

dex1: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

dex1: Its ribbonlike feelers give off an aura that weakens hostility in its prey, causing them to let down their guard. Then it attacks.

dex1: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.

dex1: Born from the high temperatures and pressures deep underground, it defends itself by firing beams from the jewel part of its body.

dex1: The weakest of all Dragon-type Pokémon, it’s unable to breathe if its skin dries out, so it sticks to shady places.

dex1: An amazingly friendly Pokémon, but if left to itself, loneliness overcomes it, and it oozes gooey tears.

dex1: These Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died in the forest. Their cries sound like eerie screams.

dex1: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

dex1: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

dex1: It blocks opponents’ attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.

dex1: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

dex1: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

dex1: This is Zygarde’s form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.

dex1: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

dex1: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

dex1: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

dex1: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.

dex1: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.

dex1: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it’s not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer’s orders with complete nonchalance.

dex1: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It’s famous for being a hard worker.

dex1: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.

dex1: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.

dex1: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.

dex1: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

dex1: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.

dex1: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it’s always snoozing by nightfall.

dex1: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and slurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.

dex1: Its body is capable of storing electricity. On camping trips, people are grateful to have one around.

dex1: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.

dex1: While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.

dex1: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.

dex1: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

dex1: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.

dex1: It’s considered to be a good Pokémon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.

dex1: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.

dex1: When it’s in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.

dex1: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

dex1: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.

dex1: The mud stuck to Mudbray’s hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.

dex1: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.

dex1: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.

dex1: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.

dex1: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis’s vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

dex1: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

dex1: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

dex1: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.

dex1: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.
dex2: A touch from anyone except a known friend sends it into a surging frenzy. It’s an incredibly dangerous Pokémon.

dex1: This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.
dex2: This Pokémon has the habit of hugging its companions. Many Trainers have left this world after their spines were squashed by its hug.

dex1: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.
dex2: Although it’s too sugary for human consumption, Bounsweet’s sweat can be watered down into a juice with just the right amount of sweetness.

dex1: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.
dex2: This Pokémon is always bouncing around energetically. Other Pokémon are attracted by its lively appearance and pleasant aroma.

dex1: Its long, striking legs aren’t just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.
dex2: A Pokémon known for the beauty of its well-shaped legs, it sometimes appears as a mascot in advertisements for beauty salons.

dex1: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.
dex2: Baths prepared with the flowers from its vine have a relaxing effect, so this Pokémon is a hit with many people.

dex1: Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it’s best suited to veteran Trainers.
dex2: Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.

dex1: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.
dex2: They battle with hard berries for weapons. Their techniques are passed from the boss to the group, generation upon generation.

dex1: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.
dex2: Its habitat varies from beaches to seabeds. A natural scavenger, it will gleefully chow down on anything edible, no matter how rotten.

dex1: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.
dex2: It battles skillfully with its six arms, but spends most of its time peacefully meditating in caves deep beneath the sea.

dex1: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokémon embodies the grudges of the departed.
dex2: It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.

dex1: Possessed people controlled by this Pokémon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.
dex2: Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.

dex1: It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.
dex2: These Pokémon line the beaches. The sticky mucous that covers their bodies can be used to soothe sunburned skin. How convenient!

dex1: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.
dex2: Due to the danger that this synthetic Pokémon may go on a rampage, it wears a control mask to restrain its power.

dex1: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.
dex2: Although its name was Type: Null at first, the boy who evolved it into this form gave it the name by which it is now known.

dex1: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.
dex2: Strong impacts can knock it out of its shell. This Pokémon was born from mutated nanoparticles.

dex1: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.
dex2: The log it holds was given to it by its parents at birth. It has also been known to cling to the arm of a friendly Trainer.

dex1: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.
dex2: It gushes fire and poisonous gases from its nostrils. Its dung is an explosive substance and can be put to various uses.

dex1: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.
dex2: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.

dex1: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.
dex2: A lonely Pokémon, it conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and other Pokémon.

dex1: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.
dex2: It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder’s shell is no match for it.

dex1: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.
dex2: This Pokémon is friendly to people and loves children most of all. It comes from deep in the mountains to play with children it likes in town.

dex1: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.
dex2: The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokémon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.

dex1: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.
dex2: They live in mountains where no trace of humans can be detected. Jangmo-o grow little by little as they battle one another.

dex1: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.
dex2: It sheds and regrows its scales on a continuous basis. The scales become harder and sharper each time they’re regrown.

dex1: When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.
dex2: Its rigid scales function as offense and defense. In the past, its scales were processed and used to make weapons and other commodities.

dex1: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.
dex2: It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.

dex1: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.
dex2: As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.

dex1: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.
dex2: The guardian deity of Ula’ula is a lazy Pokémon. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then deals them a savage blow with its horns.

dex1: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.
dex2: The guardian deity of Poni, it can control water. People say it can create pure water that will wash away any uncleanness.

dex1: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.
dex2: In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It’s said to be a Pokémon from another world, but no specific details are known.

dex1: Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.
dex2: There’s something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokémon may come from another world.

dex1: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.
dex2: This Pokémon is said to be a male evolution of Cosmog. At the activation of its third eye, it departs for another world.

dex1: It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog. When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world.
dex2: Said to live in another world, this Pokémon devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of night over the brightness of day.

dex1: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent.
dex2: One of the Ultra Beasts. It’s unclear whether or not this Pokémon is sentient, but sometimes it can be observed behaving like a young girl.

dex1: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.
dex2: A mysterious life-form called an Ultra Beast. Witnesses saw it pulverize a dump truck with a single punch.

dex1: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.
dex2: One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.

dex1: One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.
dex2: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a power plant, so people think it energizes itself with electricity.

dex1: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnesses observed it flying across the sky at high speed.
dex2: One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.

dex1: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.
dex2: One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower with one stroke of its blade.

dex1: It has gobbled mountains and swallowed whole buildings, according to reports. It’s one of the Ultra Beasts.
dex2: A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating constantly, but for some reason its droppings have never been found.

dex1: Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form, apparently asleep underground, is thought to have come from another world in ancient times.
dex2: Light is apparently the source of its energy. It has an extraordinarily vicious disposition and is constantly firing off laser beams.

dex1: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.
dex2: Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.

dex1: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.
dex2: It lurks in the shadows of others, copying their movements and powers. This Pokémon is craven and cowering.
